- The linter flake8 has an enforcement of 100 chars lines, do not exceed 100 characters per line written.
- Use 3.10 Pythonista approaches to write your code
- When in doubt, run the linter flake8
- If you need to validate that a code is ready to be shipped, create a commit to the master branch in the local Git repo, this will trigger pre-commit and let you know if anything is wrong.
- If a file is going to be bigger than 400 lines, split it.
- If it is a new chat/session, always check for the above rules.
- Keep the [tasks-list.md](mdc:tasks-list.md) file up-to-date with whatever you do, also keep track of possible improvements
- Keep your explanations short, no need to over elaborate over things unless it is something complex that needs the data to be shown and mentioned.
